Olalekan Adetayo, Abuja Members of the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 on Wednesday briefed the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), on ongoing efforts to curtail further spread of coronavirus and the way forward. They were led to the meeting that was held inside the Presidential Villa, Abuja by their chairman, Boss Mustapha, who is also the Secretary to the Government of the Federation. Others at the meeting are the PTF’s national coordinator, Sani Aliyu; the Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire; and the Director-General of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, Chikwe Ihekweazu. The meeting is coming ahead of Thursday’s announcement of new protocols by the task force